<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,399,1271,1297]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Platicrista angustata</emphasis>
(Murray 
<number box="[523,583,1271,1297]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1905.0">1905</number>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1271,1458]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
No special morphological variation was noted. Eight out of the ten specimens collected showed ocular spots. Mean body size was 
<number box="[476,520,1352,1378]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="938.0">938</number>
μm (SD 
<number box="[631,678,1352,1378]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="127.0">127</number>
), range 
<number box="[774,916,1352,1378]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1111.0" valueMax="1628.0" valueMin="594.0">594 to 1628</number>
μm. The species has been cited for Europe, Asia, 
<collectingCountry box="[221,325,1392,1418]" name="United States of America" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">America</collectingCountry>
, Africa and the Arctic. This is the first record for the Iberian Peninsula (
<tableCitation box="[1195,1288,1392,1418]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,239,1706,1730]" captionTargetBox="[159,1400,1802,1996]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 2. Tardigrada species found in the Sierra de Guadarrama. New records (NR) for Europe (Eur), the Iberian Peninsula (IbPn), Spain (Spn) and Madrid Province (Mad) are indicated." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF5C665F3D5AFF91FF689BECFC06F97C" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" tableUuid="DF5C665F3D5AFF91FF689BECFC06F97C">
Table 
<number box="[1271,1288,1392,1418]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2.0">2</number>
</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Eutardigrada" family="Hypsibiidae" genus="Platicrista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Parachela" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="angustata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Platicrista angustata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appeared at six sampling points (Table 
<number box="[732,747,1432,1458]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="3.0">3</number>
) from LF and MR samples.
</paragraph>
